The genus is very distinctive in having the following characteristics of the adults (see also Table 
1
): 1) antennae 6-segmented; 2) pronotal median groove very thin and shallow; 3) pronotal sublateral carinae absent; 4) lateral declivity of the pronotum with oblique impressions; 5) each elytron with one sublateral carina on interval VIII. The larva is also distinctive in having Y-shaped projections (Fig. 
7A, E, D
) on the thorax and abdomen.
